                                                                                              NIST SP 800-37, REVISION 2       RISK MANAGEMENT FRAMEWORK FOR INFORMATION SYSTEMS AND ORGANIZATIONS
                                                                                                                                                              A System Life Cycle Approach for Security and Privacy
                                                                                              ________________________________________________________________________________________________

                                                                                               control inheritance          A situation in which a system or application receives protection
                                                                                                                            from controls (or portions of controls) that are developed,
                                                                                                                            implemented, assessed, authorized, and monitored by entities
                                                                                                                            other than those responsible for the system or application;
                                                                                                                            entities either internal or external to the organization where the
                                                                                                                            system or application resides. See common control.
                                                                                               control parameter            See organization-defined control parameter.
                                                                                               controlled unclassified      Information that the Government creates or possesses, or that
                                                                                               information                  an entity creates or possesses for or on behalf of the
                                                                                               [32 CFR 2002.4]
                                                                                                                            Government, that a law, regulation, or Government-wide policy
                                                                                                                            requires or permits an agency to handle using safeguarding or
This publication is available free of charge from: https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.SP.800-37r2




                                                                                                                            dissemination controls. However, CUI does not include classified
                                                                                                                            information or information a non-executive branch entity
                                                                                                                            possesses and maintains in its own systems that did not come
                                                                                                                            from, or was not created or possessed by or for, an executive
                                                                                                                            branch agency or an entity acting for an agency.
                                                                                               countermeasures              Actions, devices, procedures, techniques, or other measures that
                                                                                               [FIPS 200]                   reduce the vulnerability of a system. Synonymous with security
                                                                                                                            controls and safeguards.
                                                                                               cybersecurity                Prevention of damage to, protection of, and restoration of
                                                                                               [OMB A-130]                  computers, electronic communications systems, electronic
                                                                                                                            communications services, wire communication, and electronic
                                                                                                                            communication, including information contained therein, to
                                                                                                                            ensure its availability, integrity, authentication, confidentiality,
                                                                                                                            and nonrepudiation.
                                                                                               cybersecurity framework      A risk-based approach to reducing cybersecurity risk composed
                                                                                               [NIST CSF]                   of three parts: the Framework Core, the Framework Profile, and
                                                                                                                            the Framework Implementation Tiers.
                                                                                               cybersecurity framework      The subdivision of a Function into groups of cybersecurity
                                                                                               category                     outcomes, closely tied to programmatic needs and particular
                                                                                               [NIST CSF]                   activities.
                                                                                               cybersecurity framework      A set of cybersecurity activities and references that are common
                                                                                               core                         across critical infrastructure sectors and are organized around
                                                                                               [NIST CSF]                   particular outcomes. The Framework Core comprises four types
                                                                                                                            of elements: Functions, Categories, Subcategories, and
                                                                                                                            Informative References.
                                                                                               cybersecurity framework      One of the main components of the Framework. Functions
                                                                                               function                     provide the highest level of structure for organizing basic
                                                                                               [NIST CSF]                   cybersecurity activities into Categories and Subcategories. The
                                                                                                                            five functions are Identify, Protect, Detect, Respond, and
                                                                                                                            Recover.




